Production

Having trouble with their line up, Abominable Putridity went back and forth between band members before releasing their second album. It was recorded at Cube-Zero Studio in the year of 2010, and was finalized at Anthropocide Studio a year later. Big Chocolate would have been the vocalist on the record, had it not been for Matti Way making his replacement merely weeks before writing for the album took place.
